\lambda,\mu\in\mathbb{C}
   \begin{cases}     M&=& \lambda A+\mu B \\     M^2&=& \lambda^2 A+\mu^2 B \\     M^3&=& \lambda^3 A +\mu^3 B   \end{cases} \Rightarrow M\ \text{is diagonalizable}.
P(X)=X(X-\lambda)(X-\mu)
P(M)=0
